OL,3,CBeattie 'no confidence' in Irish
OL,4,CGovernment Troubles legacy role
OL,6,F"Here's why, because the former Irish
OL,7,Fjustice minister (Michael McDowell)
OL,8,Fmade it clear in 2021 when he said the
OL,9,Fgovernment has decided it is no longer
OL,10,Fin the state's interest to investigate
OL,11,Fand prosecute Troubles-related crimes.
OL,13,F"Yet the Irish Government stands with
OL,14,Ftheir hands in their pockets
OL,15,Fcomplaining about the UK Government's
OL,16,Flegacy (policy) while they do
OL,17,Fabsolutely nothing."
OL,19,FMr Beattie referred to the 1998 Omagh
OL,20,Fbomb atrocity, which killed 29 people,
OL,21,Fincluding a mother pregnant with twins.
