OL,6,FHe said: "The Irish have not done
OL,7,Fenough, if anything whatsoever.
OL,9,F"The Omagh bomb was constructed in
OL,10,FIreland, the explosives sourced in
OL,11,FIreland, the timer power unit built in
OL,12,FIreland, the car was stolen in
OL,13,FIreland, the murderous operation was
OL,14,Fplanned and mounted from Ireland, and
OL,15,Fthe murderers, the perpetrators,
OL,16,Freturned to Ireland, yet the Irish
OL,17,FGovernment thinks it is nothing to do
OL,18,Fwith them.
OL,20,F"It is utterly scandalous."
